HEADWORD: Hesp
<hw>Hesp</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Icel.
<ets>hespa</ets> a hasp, a wisp or skein. See <er>Hasp</er>.]</ety>
<def>A measure of two hanks of linen thread.</def> <mark>[Scot.]</mark>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>hasp</asp>.]</altsp>
<rj><au>Knight.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
